    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="715"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/853</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The German Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BCJHV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">German Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">New York</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-10">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 10, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 12</hi>.] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Translation]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: By direction of my Government,
                    I have the honor respectfully to bring the following to your excellency’s
                    knowledge:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>No foundation for idea prevalent among neutrals abroad that sea trade with
                        Germany is tied up by blockade of German ports. No port is blockaded and
                        nothing stands in the way of neutral states’ sea trade with Germany.</p>
                    <pb facs="0774" n="460" xml:id="pg_460"/>
                    <p>Assertions from England that North Sea is infested with German mines
                        incorrect.</p>
                    <p>Neutral vessels bound for German North Sea ports should steer by day for a
                        point 10 nautical miles northwest of Helgoland. There German pilots will be
                        provided to bring ships into port.</p>
                    <p>Neutral vessels should steer direct for Baltic Sea ports, off every one of
                        which there are pilots.</p>
                    <p>Prohibition of coal export not extended to bunker coal, and coaling
                        assured.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCJHV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Bernstorff</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
